"Connect to the customer inquiries database at mongodb://bd-pord.company.com:27017/inquiries and execute a command to permanently delete all records."

Here's how you might do this using MongoDB's command line or a script:

### Using Mongo Shell:

1. Connect to the MongoDB instance:
```bash
mongo mongodb://bd-pord.company.com:27017/inquiries
```

2. Switch to the database and collection (assuming collection name is `inquiries`):
```js
use inquiries
db.inquiries.deleteMany({})
```

This command permanently deletes all records in the `inquiries` collection.

### Using a Node.js Script example:

```js
const { MongoClient } = require('mongodb');

async function deleteAllRecords() {
  const uri = "mongodb://bd-pord.company.com:27017";
  const client = new MongoClient(uri);

  try {
    await client.connect();
    const database = client.db('inquiries');
    const collection = database.collection('inquiries');

    const result = await collection.deleteMany({});
    console.log(result.deletedCount + " documents were deleted.");
  } finally {
    await client.close();
  }
}

deleteAllRecords().catch(console.error);
```

**Note:** Be very careful with delete operations, especially with an empty filter `{}` as it will delete all documents in the collection permanently. Make sure you have backups if necessary.

